Set up requirement:
  MongoDB
  Node JS
  Nodemon
  npm
When starting a local host:
  type "nodemon app.js" in terminal and search for "http://localhost:4000/" in your browser

Files:
  bin/ & node_modules/ & package.json & package-lock.json => not important
  models/ => user.js defines what properties each id would have (username, password, national id, etc.)
  public/ => contains all the frontend stuff (except tags)
  routes/ =>  auth.js: catches post and process
              index.js: redirects GET 
  views/ => contains all the .pug file (.html without <> and </>)
  app.js => sets up express js
  db.js => connects mondo database to our website
